
[1]commandment

   COMMANDMENT, n.

   1. A command; a mandate; an order or injunction given by authority;
   charge; precept.

   Why do ye transgress the commandment of God. Matt. 15.

   This is the first and great commandment. Matt. 22.

   A new commandment I give to you, that you love one another. John 13.

   2. By way of eminence, a precept of the decalogue, or moral law,
   written on tables of stone, at Mount Sinai; one of the ten
   commandments. Ex. 34.

   3. Authority; coercive power.
